# üêû bug report

### Affected Package

This issue is caused by @angular/service-worker

### Description

I am trying to clear the service worker caches after a new app is deployed. I am using http-server to deploy it on localhost. I have an angular app already running, and my service-worker is registered. When I change some code and redeploy the app, what I see in the cache memory is that the older cache is still present. In the cache manifest I see an array of the ngsw.json files. There is "latest" tab where the latest hash is stored. The app is rendered from the latest manifest hash, but sometimes, it gets rendered from the older manifests too. I am unable to reproduce that case, but it happens very rarely. After 10-15 mins, the manifest gets cleared and only one manifest hash is present in the cache storage. This is happening randomly without any consistency.


## üî¨ Minimal Reproduction
Create any angular app with angular service worker running, change some code, redeploy it, and you will see that the older service worker cache manifest are still present.

If I check the "Update On Reload" under the service worker tab, the older cache manifests are getting cleared instantly. I would like the older cache to be deleted by the angular service worker instantly without checking that option.

This is how my ngsw-config looks like:

<pre><code>
